The article is a letter from President Barack Obama to the Speaker of the House of Representatives and the President Pro Tempore of the Senate. In the letter, the President informs them about the targeted airstrikes conducted by U.S. Armed Forces in Iraq. The airstrikes were carried out to stop the advance of the terrorist group ISIL, support civilians trapped on Mount Sinjar, assist Iraqi forces in recapturing the Mosul Dam, and deliver humanitarian aid to civilians in the town of Amirli. The President states that these actions are in the national security and foreign policy interests of the United States and are being done in coordination with the Iraqi government. The President provides this report to keep Congress informed, as required by the War Powers Resolution.